article.headline: LIU Brooklyn 67, Lehigh 54
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Brandon Thomas scored 16 points on 7-for-11 shooting to lead Long Island University over Lehigh 67-54 on Friday night. Long Island (1-0) took a 41-29 halftime lead after shooting 55 percent from the field. Lehigh made just 33 percent of its shots in the first half and only 22 percent in the second. Lehigh (0-1) was led by Earl Nurse and Dayne Mickelson with 11 points each. Lehigh shot just 2-of-17 from 3-point range. Raymond Edwards had 10 rebounds for Long Island.
